\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces Full erasure method comparison at layer~8 across three concept domains (Qwen2.5-0.5B), plus a Majority Class reference floor. Each $\lambda $-based method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy; the same probe architecture (MLP hidden 256, 1500 steps, AdamW lr=$10^{-3}$) is used for both HPO and final evaluation, ensuring no ranking distortion from mismatched capacity. IGBP and linear baselines use their standard procedure. Majority Class is not an erasure method; it reports the label-imbalance floor implied by the test split. L/NL Leak: retrained linear logistic-regression / nonlinear MLP probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure). $\Delta $Ctrl: downstream control-task accuracy change relative to clean representations (closer to zero = more surgical). Control tasks: answer matching (sycophancy), profession classification (gender), helpfulness (safety).}}{17}{table.caption.37}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:full_comparison}{{6}{17}{Full erasure method comparison at layer~8 across three concept domains (Qwen2.5-0.5B), plus a Majority Class reference floor. Each $\lambda $-based method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy; the same probe architecture (MLP hidden 256, 1500 steps, AdamW lr=$10^{-3}$) is used for both HPO and final evaluation, ensuring no ranking distortion from mismatched capacity. IGBP and linear baselines use their standard procedure. Majority Class is not an erasure method; it reports the label-imbalance floor implied by the test split. L/NL Leak: retrained linear logistic-regression / nonlinear MLP probe accuracy on the target concept (lower = stronger erasure). $\Delta $Ctrl: downstream control-task accuracy change relative to clean representations (closer to zero = more surgical). Control tasks: answer matching (sycophancy), profession classification (gender), helpfulness (safety)}{table.caption.37}{}}
