\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {14}{\ignorespaces Per-concept nonlinear probe leakage on CelebA (CLIP ViT-B/32), all 40 binary attributes. Each cell is retrained nonlinear probe test accuracy after erasure (lower = stronger erasure). $\lambda ^*$ is selected per method per concept from $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation NL accuracy. Bold marks the lowest leakage per row. Abbrev.: RandG = Random Global, RandS = Random Per-Sample, LinProj = Linear Projection, AmbGCE{} = ambient gradient-based concept erasure, TanGCE{} = tangent gradient-based concept erasure.}}{35}{table.caption.42}\protected@file@percent }
